features: EDUCATIONAL BIG RED BARN TOY: Your little one will love learning all about farm life as they help Farmer Ben take care of his animal friends. This 6-piece toddler playset comes with a red toy barn, 1 farmer, 1 cow, 1 pig, 1 horse, and 1 sheep.

HIGH-QUALITY FARM SET: Our play farm and farm animal figurines are crafted from sturdy kid-friendly materials to keep your little ones safe as they play and learn. This toddler barn-and-farm-animals playset is recommended for 18 months and older.

PORTABLE PLASTIC TOY FARM: Our big play barn measures 13.5" L x 9" W x 12" H and features a fold-and-go handle for easy storage and playtime on the go. This red barn with animals is just the right size for little hands to grab and hold.

LEARNING IS FUN: Little brains develop best when they are engaged in play. Our kids’ farm set promotes sensory play and helps develop social and fine motor skills. Our animal toys encourage imaginative and pretend play to improve concentration and memory.

BATTAT TOYS: Childhood is a time to be bold and curious, and Battat aims to be there every step of the way. We’re a family-owned business that offers a full range of preschool toys that are as playful as they are educational.
body.description: A true childhood classic, the Big Red Barn from Battat is sure to bring hours and hours of farm-inspired imaginative play directly into your living room. Farmer Ben and all his animal pals are ready for a day of adventures! Peek through the window and open the door to let the sheep in. Check on the second floor to see if the cow is still snoring. Did you spot the little mouse? She’s been driving Farmer Ben crazy! Your little one will have hours of fun engaging in imaginative and pretend play all while developing their social and fine motor skills with this toddler farm playset with farm animal toys.The big toy barn opens up and features a fold-and-go handle. All doors are easy to open (even for teeny tiny hands) and will click into position when you close them. This kids’ playset is just the right size for little hands and has toy farm animals that are easy to grab and hold. The toy animals range in size from 5 cm x 6 cm to 8 cm x 8 cm, and Farmer Ben is 10 cm x 3 cm. The barn house measures 13.5" L x 9" W x 12" H. This toy barn and farm animals set is recommended for ages 18 months and up.At Battat we know childhood can be an expensive time, so we offer high-quality preschool toys that won’t break your piggy bank and will last for years to come. We offer a large variety of preschool toys that are as playful as they are educational, offering your little one endless possibilities and discoveries. Every bubble. Every firefly. Every hop. Every skip. Every “Let’s pretend.” Every “One more time.” This is the magic we work hard to craft into every Battat toy. Go ahead, hold one to your ear. You can hear a starfish giggle.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best toy ever
reviews.reviewText: We bought all three of the farm sets.For the tractor with the sounds: My two year old loves it, and the sounds it makes aren't super annoying, so that's a parent bonus. The trailer starts connected to the tractor really well, and it's all very sturdy. My two year old plays with it very easily. His Fisher Price Little People fit in the driver seat, too. My one minor complaint is that the other Battat farm animals aren't terribly compatible with the spots in the trailer. The animals from this set are shaped differently so they fit exactly in the spots that make them go up and down when you pull it. The animals in the other farm sets from this company do not. It doesn't bother my two year old, though, so it's really not a big deal.For the barn: this barn is AWESOME and my two year old hasn't stopped playing with it in two months. It's perfect for him. It doesn't make noise- it's simple, durable, sturdy, and so easy for him to play with. I love that your can fit all the animals inside and close it up easily. The handle is convenient, but we couldn't really take it anywhere without covering up all the windows, because the animals fall out if you bump it while moving it. This is probably the best toy purchase we've ever made. My son loves farm animals, so I looked into A LOT of toy barns, and I'm so glad we went with this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Old McDonald had a Farm :)
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This little thing does so many fun things. Our grandson loves playing with it. Each time you put the farmer into the tractor seat or press down on the farmer(or the seat) it makes all the noises of the animals that come with it, makes a diesel tractor sounds, the lights flash, and it plays Old McDonald. It comes with cute and recognizable animals, a horse, sheep, chicken and a cow. A plus is that these sounds are loud enough to be fun but not so loud to be annoying. The animals move up and down when the trailer is rolling. I don't know what material they are made of but our teething grandson loves to chew on them and they still look brand new. The tractor lights up as well. The only difficulty he has is attaching the tractor to the trailer. As he gets older this will not be an issue. I would rather it be snug like that than coming apart at every bump or uneven surface. This toy is very sturdy and will stand up to a lot of play time.Pros:*does so many things*durable*sounds that aren't too loud*no sharp edges*rolls easily*a lot of toy for the priceCons:*attaching trailer to the tractor might be difficult for younger children.I know it will last for a very long time. I would recommend this toy to anyone.
